At the beginning of Farmet’s history there was a desire to do something useful.
And so when the state proposed to Karel Zdrasky's father to rent the small workshop as compensation after the confiscation of property by the communists, he did not hesitate for long, refused a career in a firm where he worked at the time, and created a company with a few comrades in his father's entourage for the manufacture of plastic bathtubs.
Not long after they began to specialize in presses for vegetable oil.
After 18 years, it became the largest manufacturer of automatic presses in Central Europe.
The company was known even in the non-specialist public after the success achieved in the contest through the media.
“Not only did our customers really get to know the Farmet brand better, but also the foreign partners who began to realize that they were collaborating with a company that achieved the greatest success in its home country,” says Karel Zdarsky.
