Fernet, rum, vodka and exceptionally the best brand of whisky are stolen from parents.
These are drinks that most often bring those who are drunk, who are not yet fifteen years old, into the hands of the doctor.
Children who are treated in hospital for recidivism are no exception.
This results from the experience of physicians who encounter cases similar to admissions from children's departments of hospitals.
“Beer or wine is no longer fashionable because it takes time to get drunk.”
“The trend is really for strong alcohols,” says Pravo Ludek Pelikan, head of the children’s department at the Horovice hospital in central Bohemia.
