Eva Jurinova, a spokeswoman for the Motol hospital, is also right.
"In general, it's rum or fernet."
"It's now the fashionable alcohol, especially in elementary schools."
"In some cases, it was a slivovice that they brought back from the house," Jurinova added.
According to department head Pelikan, seeing drunk children between the ages of thirteen and fourteen in hospital admissions is a normal phenomenon.
