It is precisely the parents' disinterestedness or their extraordinary tolerance for the fact that their offspring indulge in drinking that are the main cause of the development of children's alcoholism.
According to specialists, however, there is no talk of addiction, in its strict sense, for children.
"Under the word alcoholic we mean a chronic dependence on alcohol of several years with all the phenomena that arise from it but that is not found in children."
"In those who use acool repeatedly, it is rather a significantly unfavorable socio-family background," said Pelikan.
According to spokeswoman Jurinova, about forty drunk children were hospitalized this year until mid-November at the pediatric clinic in Motol.
Only cases with severe intoxication requiring hospitalization are integrated into the statistics.
Drunk children who are after emergency care taken home by parents or the police are not counted.
In addition to the cases of children who sit down and drink a bottle of alcohol after school, according to Pélikan, he excites three seasonal waves with which one can count: the day of the witches, Christmas Eve and the end of the school year.
“Either they drink out of spite after bad results or on the contrary they celebrate the start of the holiday.”
