Americans have a new "smart weapon"
The U.S. military has sent a new "smart" weapon to Afghanistan, known only as the XM-25 code.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will have an influence on the conflict there with the Taliban and “will change the game” for their benefit.
The new weapon is like a super accurate cannon
Its projectiles are guided by laser with a precision of a few meters.
The special 25mm calibre ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly-breaking explosive, actually works like small grenades.
